snippet.description: Whether you fancy trendy city cars or crazy customs ripped from a comic book, there are plenty to go

snippet.title: Best laptops
snippet.description: CNET editors choose and review the best thin and light laptops, notebooks, and ultrabooks.

snippet.title: iLuv City Lights in-ear headphones
snippet.description: For around $7, the iLuv City Lights are well-designed budget earphones, but they push the bass a little too hard at the expense of clarity.

snippet.title: Batman: Arkham City - Armored Edition (Wii U)
snippet.description: The Wii U-specific additions put a few chinks in the Caped Crusader's costume, but Batman: Arkham City - Armored Edition is still a great action adventure game.

snippet.title: LEGO City Undercover (Wii U)
snippet.description: If you don't mind waiting for the game to load, Lego City: Undercover has a lot of fun packed inside, even if most of the gameplay is stuff you might have seen before.

snippet.title: Groopic for iOS
snippet.description: Groopic is a must-have for getting the photographer into a group shot, with an easy-to-understand process, filters to spice up your picture, and mostly flawless results.

snippet.title: Thor as metal-factory worker? Superheroes get part-time jobs
snippet.description: A geeky illustrator imagines the perfect everyday jobs for superheroes who might need a break from all the danger and glitz. Who knows? Superman could end up in the cubicle next to yours.

snippet.title: Apple AirPort Time Capsule
snippet.description: As long as you don't need expert-level features, the 2013 AirPort Time Capsule is an excellent backup/file server for Apple fans -- especially for those with 802.11ac-enabled Macs.

snippet.title: 2014 Scion iQ
snippet.description: Because of its size, the 2014 Scion iQ makes for an exceptional city car, and its cabin electronics will satisfy most, but put it at the bottom of the list as a long-distance road trip car.

snippet.title: No books here: New Texas library is all digital
snippet.description: San Antonio's BiblioTech, believed to be the first public bookless library in the US, offers computers, Internet access, e-readers, and technology classes.
